                <span class="field-content"><a href="../library/chinafaqs-what-are-chinas-national-climate-and-energy-targets">ChinaFAQs:  What Are China&#039;s National Climate and Energy Targets?</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/ChinaFAQs_table_China_climate_energy_targets-1.jpg" alt="" title="" width="155" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"><div class="filefield-file"><img class="filefield-icon field-icon-application-pdf"  alt="application/pdf icon" src="../sites/all/modules/filefield/icons/application-pdf.png" /><a href="../files/chinainfo/ChinaFAQs_table_China_climate_energy_targets_0.pdf" type="application/pdf; length=194275">ChinaFAQs_table_China_climate_energy_targets.pdf</a></div></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p><b>Key Points:</b></p>

<ul><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><li>China has a long term target to reduce the carbon intensity of the economy by 40-45% from 2005 levels by 2020</li>
<li>China also has binding targets to reduce energy intensity by 16% from 2010 levels by 2015 and carbon intensity by 17% from 2010 levels by 2015</li>
<li>China has a target to reduce coal consumption as a percentage of primary energy to below 65% by 2017</li>
<li>China has ambitious targets for renewable energy in 2015, 2017, and 2020</li></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote></ul></div>
  </div>
  </div>
