  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>China‚Äôs 12th Five Year Plan includes an array of energy targets that it hopes to achieve by 2015.  The targets, such as increasing the share of non-fossil energy to 11.4% of the total energy supply and cutting the economy‚Äôs carbon intensity by 17% by 2015, are part of a larger plan for China to reach a 40-45% reduction in carbon intensity by 2020 relative to 2005 levels.  ChinaFAQs expert Trevor Houser has crunched the numbers provided by China‚Äôs National Bureau of Statistics and come up with a report card on the country‚Äôs progress towards achieving its climate and energy goals.</p></div>
