  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>The latest International Energy Agency‚Äôs (IEA) <em><a href="http://www.iea.org/newsroomandevents/pressreleases/2012/december/name,34441,en.html">Medium-Term Coal Market Report 2012</a></em> re-confirms the dangerous path the world is on&#8211;a path of increasing dependence on coal, which carries serious environmental risks for people and the planet. According to <a href="http://www.iea.org/newsroomandevents/pressreleases/2012/december/name,34441,en.html">the report</a>, the world will burn 1.2 billion metric tons more coal per year by 2017 compared to today, surpassing oil as the world‚Äôs top energy source.</p></div>
