  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>On October 12, ChinaFAQs and the <b><a href="http://www.eesi.org/101212_China">Environmental and Energy Study Institute (EESI)</a></b> held a briefing on Capitol Hill about the issues driving China‚Äôs renewable energy, energy efficiency, and climate policies. While China and the United States differ in important respects, they have some similar challenges and opportunities relating to energy. Both face economic, employment, energy security, and environmental challenges. The United States and China both cooperate and compete with each other on clean energy initiatives and technology.</p></div>
