  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../blog-posts/what-can-we-expect-climate-and-energy-china-2011">What Can We Expect on Climate and Energy in China in 2011?</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/2011_1-5-11.jpg" alt="" title="" width="194" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>2011 will be a big year for climate and energy policy development in China, so we thought we‚Äôd highlight some of the key China energy and climate-related stories to watch out for during the course of the year.  We‚Äôve known to expect major developments now for over a year, since China‚Äôs commitments made at the Copenhagen climate talks in late 2009 were scheduled to be implemented in the 2011 12th Five Year Plan.</p></div>
  </div>
