  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../blog-posts/china-and-india-now-associated-copenhagen-accord">China and India Now Associated with the Copenhagen Accord</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>China <a href="../blog-posts/following-copenhangen-accord-china-submits-carbon-intensity-target-unfccc-secretariat">reported its commitment to a 40-45% reduction in carbon intensity by 2020</a>, based on a 2005 baseline, by the Copenhagen Accord‚Äôs January 31 deadline. But there was still some ambiguity about China‚Äôs actual relationship to the Copenhagen Accord itself.  Now China and India, as well, have written the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (UNFCCC) Secretariat.</p></div>
  </div>
